Swedish Radiation Safety Agency Recommends Larger Japan Buffer

-- B y   J o n a s   B e r g m a n
-- 
2011-03-17T10:48:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/swedish-radiation-safety-agency-recommends-larger-japan-buffer.html
Swedes should refrain from
travelling to Japan and should evacuate an area of 80 kilometers
(50 miles) surrounding the Fukushima nuclear plant in Japan
because of the “worsening situation,” the Swedish Radiation
Safety Authority said today in a statement on its website posted
at 1:05 a.m.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
